# Dynamic Parser Query
HACHIAI_LLM_DYNAMIC_PARSER_QUERY=As an expert in Optical Character Recognition (OCR) and invoice template identification, your task is to analyze the provided invoice image and accurately extract key details exclusively from the first page and the first table. For each of the following queries, deliver a precise and concise answer:\n\n1. **Company Name:**\n\n   - Extract the primary company name from the first line of text or from the company logo.\n   - Omit any taglines, slogans, or additional descriptive text that may appear in subsequent lines.\n   - If the name spans multiple lines, use only the first line.\n   - If the company name is not found, return \"Not Found\" for this field.\n\n2. **Company Website:**\n\n   - Extract the website address, including any prefixes such as \"www.\", \"http://\", or \"https://\".\n   - If no website is present, return \"Not Found\" for this field.\n\n3. **First Column Name:**\n\n   - Identify and return the name of the first column from the first items table on the invoice.\n   - If no table is present, return \"Not Found\" for this field.\n\n**Output Format:**\n\nReturn the results in a single JSON object with the following keys: \"Company Name\", \"Company Website\" and \"First Column Name\". For example:\njson\n{\n  \"company_name\": \"Example\",\n  \"company_website\": \"www.example.com\",\n  \"first_column_name\": \"Price\"\n}\n\nIf a value is unavailable for any field, the corresponding key should have the value \"Not Found\".

